            "answer_text": "The owner of the copyright on the composition of a piece of music is probably the composer and/or the publisher. One of the rights in copyright is the right to make derivative works. A new arrangement is a derivative work. To make a new arrangement of the music, you will need written permission from the owner of the copyright, which is probably the composer or publisher. If and when you get that permission, creating the arrangement will be legal. ",
